ted the Beatles\' lives since 1969. Journalist Peter Doggett charts the Shakespearean battles between Lennon and McCartney, the conflict in George Harrison\'s life between spirituality and fame, and the struggle with alcoholism that threatened to take Richard Starkey\'s life. In vivid detail, Doggett also describes the wild mismanagement of the Beatles\' fortune staked largely in Apple Corps. \nYou Never Give Me Your Money is a compelling human drama and an equally rich and absorbing story of the Beatles\' creative and financial empire, set up to safeguard their interests but destined to control their lives. From tragedy to triumphant reunion, and chart success to courtroom battles, this meticulously researched work tells the previously untold story of a group and a legacy that will never be forgotten.<\/span>\n  <a data-text-id=\"8050738485178300070\" href=\"#\" onclick=\"swapContent(\$(this));; return false;\">...more<\/a>\n\n    <\/div>\n\n      <div class=\'wtrButtonContainer wtrSignedOut\' id=\'20_book_7972484\'>\n<div class=\'wtrUp wtrLeft\'>\n<form action=\"/shelf/add_to_shelf\" accept-charset=\"UTF-8\" method=\"post\"><input name=\"utf8\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"&#x2713;\" /><input type=\"hidden\" name=\"authenticity_token\" value=\"kjkVQNF9OdT/kaNVCJ0G0CzTA8s91bVzbUsxrKz/4EBHA6juxFso+EOVqRMz7rcdnrCFF8GYmflzpAoXbniFwA==\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"book_id\" id=\"book_id\" value=\"7972484\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"name\" id=\"name\" value=\"to-read\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"unique_id\" id=\"unique_id\" value=\"20_book_7972484\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"wtr_new\" id=\"wtr_new\" value=\"true\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"from_choice\" id=\"from_choice\" value=\"false\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"from_home_module\" id=\"from_home_module\" value=\"false\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"ref\" id=\"ref\" value=\"\" class=\"wtrLeftUpRef\" />\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"existing_review\" id=\"existing_review\" v